  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A habit is a tendency to act, think, or interpret in a particular way under particular circumstances. In [Peirce's](../../../../../../humanities/domains/general/domains/people/charles-sanders-peirce.md) philosophy, habit is not merely psychological but cosmological: it is the general form of regularity, the way the universe acquires its laws and the way [signs](./sign.md) acquire their meanings.",
